summary: Shiny Dratini is finished! I dont like to ship Dratini already in a pose, but in order to take a good photo of her all done I...
body: Shiny Dratini is finished! I dont like to ship Dratini already in a pose, but in order to take a good photo of her all done I had to pose her briefly~ I havent made Dratini since I made the original pair a few months ago, and I had forgotten just how quickly she works up - even as a 2ft long noodle 😆 I’ll be starting the next amigurumi later this evening, and you’ll be able to order your own Dratini when I take new orders in a few weeks at TheTallGrass.etsy.com!

summary: Decided I wanted to draw Allie as a Kanto Sandslash just for fun. :D While I figure she'd still be sensitive to the cold, being...
caption:
Decided I wanted to draw Allie as a Kanto Sandslash just for fun. :D While I figure she’d still be sensitive to the cold, being a ground type rather than an ice type means she’s not generating her own little cold spot and thus with that and Kanto’s relatively temperate-to-warm climate in mind she can wear lighter clothing on a regular basis. She wears claw gloves because, unlike the moveset I’ve got for her atm, she’d probably use more clawing attacks as well and it would help for loosening dirt to aid in ground-type moves.

Commissions ~ Redbubble ~ Patreon

~If you like, please consider reblogging to show your friends!~

summary: I’d like some advice for someone returning to the games Pokemon for the first time in several years.
title: I’d like some advice for someone returning to the games Pokemon for the first time in several years.
body:
Hey fellow trainers, as the title of this post says I haven’t picked up “the latest copy” of a Pokemon game after peal edition, and the only real reason why I decided I’d finally pick up the games again is that I need some way to entertain myself while I wait for therapy. (I’m also getting new leaf for the same reason, but that’s a much easier game to get into).

So, my copy of ultra moon is here but my new 3ds xl won’t be here until Tuesday and the copy of ultra sun that I got for my little sister won’t be here until tomorrow. I’d like to play through the game with her and, like I said, while I wait for therapy, but I don’t know how much has changed or if there’s a way that I can keep up with her. So far everyone has told me that “It’s a Pokemon game nothing has changed” but from what iv’e seen so far a lot has.

Is there any advice to give or is it as folks said and nothing has changed? 

Thanks!
